Agnes Reeves Taylor will be in the dock at London&#8217;s Old Bailey at the end of this month. PRETORIA - Agnes Reeves Taylor will be in the dock at London s Old Bailey at the end of this month to face charges of torture in Liberia between 1989 and 1991.She has also been charged with three counts of intentionally inflicting severe pain or suffering on an individual in the performance of her official duties.She s the ex-wife of former Liberian strongman Charles Taylor who s in a British jail serving a 50-year-sentence for war crimes in West Africa.She appeared at Westminster Magistrates Court last week.From 1989 to 2003, up to a quarter of a million people in Liberia were killed in a civil war, while thousands more were mutilated and raped.Additional reporting by Reuters.